10K Resistors

Resistor
    to protect LED's
    because baterry pushes a lot of electrons    too much charge!!
    with resistor, less electrons can flow around the curcuit
    the electrons collide with atoms inside the resistor and these collisions generate heat!!!

# Helical Grove Cut inside Resistor to prevent colliding...
    Shorter Cut, Low Resistance
    Longer Cut, High Resistance

LED Voltage drop = 2V
Current = 20mA    (to LED manufacturer)

Battery = 9V
Resistor Voltage Drop    9V-2V=7V
Resistor Value            7V ÷ 0.02A = 350Ω
Energy removed (from circuit (P=I^2*R))    (0.02)^2 * 350Ω = 0.14W
Min power Rating of resistor                1/4W (0.25W)


